KC didn't like it. I wonder why? I liked it. I liked the opening speech. I did not try to think that He was a villian. I wanted to believe he was fighting for good. And so I became an optomist during this episode. However as it went on I believed that by Teal'c and Bra'Tacs facial expresions even they believed something was not right.

The photography in this Episode was very good. I think that the guy the hired to play Imhotep was specially trained in Martial Arts. I would like to see this new Photography developed. It's very good. The series is constantly trying to do feature film type visuals and stories and it is being done well here. I would like to see some type of battle done with this type of Photography except it would be interesting to see a battle between two Goa'ulds with hand devices. And it should be saved for the feature, if there is to be one.

I enjoyed the funny opening line. It was just out of nowhere. Jack said something about Deliverance and asked Bra'Tac if he had seen what happened in that film. I thought this was so funny. No really. You know Ronny Cox was in that film also?

I liked Raknor's character and enjoyed seeing him once again. And I am Glad that Yu is not dead as well. I've always believed him to be the most honourable of The Goa'uld, albe he still a Goa'uld he is certainly the unbaddest as was mentioned several times above by some members.
